<p>You can checkup for the special variable <code>__name__</code> with this simple example:</p>

<p>create file1.py</p>

<pre><code>if __name__ == "__main__":
    print("file1 is being run directly")
else:
    print("file1 is being imported")
</code></pre>

<p>create file2.py</p>

<pre><code>import file1 as f1

print("__name__ from file1: {}".format(f1.__name__))
print("__name__ from file2: {}".format(__name__))

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print("file2 is being run directly")
else:
    print("file2 is being imported")
</code></pre>

<p>Execute file2.py</p>

<p><em>output</em>:</p>

<pre><code>file1 is being imported
__name__ from file1: file1
__name__ from file2: __main__
file2 is being run directly
</code></pre>
